cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with decision problems for different variants of two-dimensional automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of the language emptiness problem for unary three-way nondeterministic two-dimensional automata. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the complexity of different decision problems for two-dimensional automata. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper deals with the decidability of the language equivalence problem for two-way deterministic two-dimensional automata. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the regularity of column and row projections of two-dimensional automata.
